EUROPEAN COMMISSION PROGRAM: COOPERATION WITH DEVELOPING COUNTRIES
==================================================================
[This item is reposted from the WHO "TDR-Scientists" list. - Mod.]

I was informed of INCO-DC initiative [for cooperation with developing
countries], of the European Commission.
EUROPEAN COMMISSION
Directorate General XII
SCIENCE, RESEARCH AND DEVELOPMENT - JOINT RESEARCH CENTRE
RTD: Cooperation with non-member countries and intern'l organi.
COOPERATION WITH DEVELOPING COUNTRIES (INCO-DC)
Second call for proposals of INCO-DC is to be published on 15 March
1996, with a closing date in September 1996.
Useful URLs:
http://www.cec.lu
- gives you Homepage of the EC
http://www.cordis.lu/cgi/build_doclist.pl
and by selecting INCO entry, and "Info Package for Part C"
- gives you the detail of the first call (for proposals),
already made.
For those with email only, you can request information package by
writing to:
INFODESK.INCO@mhsg.cec.be
(source: T.J.Hall's circular letter XII-B4/TJH/cl/39393)

That's all I know so far. Not even sure it is the most relevant EC
pointers to tropical diseases researchers. There must be many windows of
grant opportunities there at EC.... Those who know more about these
opportunities, please post here (or email to me). Thanks.
--
Bob Hata, Ph.D.
Management Officer (Planning/Networking)
TDR/WHO
hata@who.ch
